    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-07-14T04:00:25+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-14T04:00:25+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-13T18:30:25Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-13T18:30:25Z">
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A ridge of high pressure lies over northern SA. A strong high pressure system will move east mid week, dominating the weather pattern until at least Friday.</text>
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-07-14T05:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-15T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-13T19:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-14T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Isolated showers about the agricultural area, clearing by evening. Maximum temperatures near average. West to southwesterly winds, easing and tending southwest to southeasterly during the day.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-07-15T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-16T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-14T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-15T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Dry. Maximum temperatures near average. Southeast to northeasterly winds.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-07-16T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-17T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-15T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-16T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Dry. Maximum temperatures near average grading to below average in the far north. Southeast to northeasterly winds.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-07-17T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-18T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-16T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-17T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">
                    <p>Dry. Maximum temperatures near average, tending above average in the west. North to northeasterly winds.</p>
                    <p/>
                    <p>Cumulative rainfall totals to the end of Friday: Generally up to 2 mm about the west coast, northern agricultural area and remaining parts of the Flinders Ranges and Eyre Peninsula, 2 to 5 mm across the southern agricultural area, with isolated falls of 5 to 15 mm about the Mount Lofty Ranges.</p>
                </text>
